message.content:
A flute is a woodwind instrument made of metal or wood with a long, narrow cylinder shape.
It has a slender and cylindrical appearance and typically has a silver or gold color.
The body of the flute has a smooth and polished texture with small key holes along the body.
It typically ranges in size from about 2 to 3 feet long and has a range of about 3 octaves.
The end of the flute has a small mouthpiece where the player blows air to produce sound.
The flute is commonly used in classical and orchestral music as well as in folk and world music traditions.
It can be found in music stores, concert halls, and recordings studios around the world.
